{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0e959b1c-1b15-47df-ae1c-6a2229d0244d","content":"The template is **mostly ready** but has a few gaps for NuGet publishing:\n\n**✅ Good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author` — all present\n- `sourceName` for namespace replacement\n- `classifications` and `tags` properly set\n- `symbols` with a valid parameter definition\n\n**⚠️ Recommended additions:**\n\n1. **`$schema`** — Missing. Add for editor validation:\n   ```json\n   \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n   ```\n\n2. **`groupIdentity`** — Missing. Important for NuGet so templates can be versioned/updated correctly (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n\n3. **No `description`** — NuGet listings look incomplete without one.\n\n**Verdict:** Functional, but add `$schema`, `groupIdentity`, and a `description` field before publishing. You'll also need a `.csproj` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>` to pack it as a template NuGet package — want me to check if that exists?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"efb93367-119d-43ca-ba18-2365d4ce480b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields.\n\nRequired fields for a .NET template:\n- `$schema` - not strictly required but highly recommended\n- `identity` - ✅ present\n- `name` - ✅ present\n- `shortName` - ✅ present\n- `author` - ✅ present (though this is technically optional, it's best practice)\n\nMissing or concerning items:\n1. **`$schema`** - Missing. Should reference `http://json.schemastore.org/template` for validation support.\n\n\n2. **`groupIdentity`** - Missing. Recommended for NuGet packages to group related templates.\n3. **`precedence`** - Missing (optional, but useful with groupIdentity).\n4. **`preferNameDirectory`** - Missing (optional).\n\nThe template has the core essentials but lacks a few recommended fields for proper NuGet distribution—specifically `$schema` for tooling support and `groupIdentity` to organize related templates.\n\nI should also consider whether there's a surrounding project structure like a .csproj file for packaging this as a NuGet template, though the user's question was focused on the template.json itself. Overall, it's functional but could use those additions for a more polished NuGet release.","outputTokens":641,"requestId":"501B:25E777:307D1C3:351B7EC:69FBE375"},"id":"24f9d036-1317-41ed-8c90-306c6bb970be","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:38.977Z","parentId":"a26ffcda-2efa-4666-bff8-58a53e440d88"}
